        {
          "scid": "an4.32:1.1",
          "pli": "“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, saṅgahavatthūni. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, there are these four ways of being inclusive. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:1.2",
          "pli": "Katamāni cattāri? ",
          "en": "What four? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:1.3",
          "pli": "Dānaṃ, peyyavajjaṃ, atthacariyā, samānattatā—",
          "en": "Giving, kindly words, taking care, and equality. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:1.4",
          "pli": "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri saṅgahavatthūnīti. ",
          "en": "These are the four ways of being inclusive. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:2.1",
          "pli": "Dānañca peyyavajjañca, ",
          "en": "Giving and kindly words, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:2.2",
          "pli": "atthacariyā ca yā idha; ",
          "en": "taking care here, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:2.3",
          "pli": "Samānattatā ca dhammesu, ",
          "en": "and equality in worldly conditions, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:2.4",
          "pli": "tattha tattha yathārahaṃ; ",
          "en": "in each case as they deserve. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:2.5",
          "pli": "Ete kho saṅgahā loke, ",
          "en": "These ways of being inclusive in the world "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:2.6",
          "pli": "rathassāṇīva yāyato. ",
          "en": "are like a moving chariot’s linchpin. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:3.1",
          "pli": "Ete ca saṅgahā nāssu, ",
          "en": "If there were no such ways of being inclusive, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:3.2",
          "pli": "na mātā puttakāraṇā; ",
          "en": "neither mother nor father "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:3.3",
          "pli": "Labhetha mānaṃ pūjaṃ vā, ",
          "en": "would be respected and honored "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:3.4",
          "pli": "pitā vā puttakāraṇā. ",
          "en": "for what they’ve done for their children. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:4.1",
          "pli": "Yasmā ca saṅgahā ete, ",
          "en": "But since these ways of being inclusive do exist, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:4.2",
          "pli": "samavekkhanti paṇḍitā; ",
          "en": "the astute do regard them well, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:4.3",
          "pli": "Tasmā mahattaṃ papponti, ",
          "en": "so they achieve greatness "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:4.4",
          "pli": "pāsaṃsā ca bhavanti te”ti. ",
          "en": "and are praised.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.32:4.5",
          "pli": "Dutiyaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
